text: On October 6, 2018, at approximately 19:11, a magnitude 5.9 earthquake struck 19 km northwest of Port-de-Paix, Haiti. The earthquake killed at least 12 people, and shaking was felt as far away as Port-au-Prince. The earthquake was the strongest to hit Haiti since January 12, 2010. ==References== Category:2018 disasters Category:2018 in North America Category:2010s disasters in North America Category:2010s in Haiti 2018 Category:October 2018 events
title: 2018 Haiti earthquake
